AND TALKING BUSINESS,
THAT FALLS AWAY.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.000
WHAT IS INTERESTING THOUGH,

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:33.000
IF I GO WITH A COLLEAGUE OR
 WITH A CLIENT INTO A RESTAURANT

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.000
AND MY PARTNER IS MALE,

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:39.000
THERE IS
 AN AUTOMATIC ASSUMPTION

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:42.000
THAT HE IS THE BOSS
 OR THE MORE SENIOR PERSON

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.000
OF THE TWO OF US.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:47.000
TO BE A BRIT IN FRANKFURT...

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:49.000
I LOVE IT,
I ABSOLUTELY LOVE IT.

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:52.000
I MEAN, IF NOW I HAD
THE CHOICE TO GO BACK TO LONDON,

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:54.000
I DON'T THINK I WOULD.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.000
I THINK IT HELPS
 THAT I SPEAK GERMAN,

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:58.000
BECAUSE IT'S A LOT EASIER
 TO MEET NEW PEOPLE

00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:00.000
AND FRANKFURT
 ITSELF IS INTERNATIONAL.

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:02.000
A LOT OF PEOPLE
 COME HERE TO WORK.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:07.000
NARRATOR: GERMANY'S DOOR
 SEEMS TO SWING OPEN

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.000
IF ONLY FOR THOSE
 WHO CAN SHOW THEY ARE NEEDED.

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:10.000
ITS ZERO GROWTH
 IMMIGRATION POLICY

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:13.000
OF THE LAST QUARTER CENTURY
 HAS FAILED.

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:14.000
THIS POLICY
 HAS ENCOURAGED THE BUSINESS

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:16.000
OF SMUGGLING
 ILLEGAL IMMIGRANTS

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:18.000
LIKE THIS YOUNG MAN
 FROM MOROCCO

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:20.000
ON HIS WAY
 TO THE FRANKFURT AIRPORT

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:21.000
ON DEPORTATION ORDERS,

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:23.000
WHILE LEAVING GERMANY
 WITH A SHORTAGE

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:26.000
OF SKILLED AN UNSKILLED LABOR.

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:31.000
I THINK
COMPANIES ARE MORE WORRIED

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:34.000
ABOUT FINDING PEOPLE TO KEEP
THE COMPUTER SYSTEM RUNNING

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:37.000
RATHER THAN, WE NEED SECURITY
GUARDS AND SECRETARIES.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:39.000
SURE, THEY NEED THEM,

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.000
BUT I THINK
 THE MORE CRITICAL NEED IS STILL

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:43.000
THE SHORTAGE
 OF HIGHLY SKILLED WORKERS.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.000
NARRATOR: EXPERTS FEEL
 THE PROBLEM WILL GET WORSE

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:47.000
AS GERMANY'S POPULATION AGES.

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:49.000
[MAN TRANSLATING GRIESHEIMER]

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.000
WE NEED MIGRATION.

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:54.000
OUR BIRTH RATE IS GOING DOWN
 AND OUR LABOR FORCE IS AGING.

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:56.000
WE CAN'T GET AROUND IT.

00:11:56.000 --> 00:11:58.000
SO, WE NEED
 AN IMMIGRATION POLICY

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:02.000
CLOSELY LINKED TO THE DEMANDS
 OF OUR LABOR MARKET.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:07.000
NARRATOR: GERMANY'S NEED
 FOR FOREIGN WORKERS

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:09.000
HAS PROVOKED
 A HEATED NATIONAL DEBATE.

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:11.000
FORCING THE GOVERNMENT
 TO MOVE CAUTIOUSLY

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:13.000
TO CHANGE
 ITS IMMIGRATION POLICY.

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:15.000
A RECENTLY INTRODUCED
 GREEN CARD PROGRAM

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.000
ALLOWS FOREIGN
 HI-TECH SPECIALISTS

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:20.000
TO WORK AND LIVE IN GERMANY
 FOR UP TO FIVE YEARS.

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:23.000
BOUDETTE: WE'VE SET ASIDE
 20,000 GREEN CARDS

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:27.000
AND THE APPLICANT MUST HAVE
EITHER A UNIVERSITY DEGREE

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.000
OR MUST BE EMPLOYED IN A JOB

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:31.000
THAT PAYS MORE THAN
A 100,000 MARKS A YEAR,

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:34.000
WHICH REALLY PRETTY MUCH
KEEPS THAT LIMITED

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:37.000
TO A FAIRLY HIGH LEVEL JOB.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:40.000
NOW SHORT TERM,
THAT DOESN'T HAVE A HUGE IMPACT

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.000
ON THE LABOR MARKET,

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:45.000
BECAUSE THERE'S ONLY FEW
GREEN CARDS WHICH ARE REQUESTED.

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:47.000
BUT LONG TERM,
I THINK, THE SIGNAL

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:49.000
IS MUCH MORE FUNDAMENTAL.

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:52.000
AND THE SIGNAL IS MORE THAN
THE SINGULAR GREEN CARD ISSUED,

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:54.000
IT IS OPENING UP
THE BORDERLINES

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:56.000
TO A FREE FLOW
OF IDEAS AND CREATIVITY

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:58.000
AMONGST NATIONS.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:12:59.000
[MAN TRANSLATING MONZ]

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:02.000
WE DON'T BELIEVE THAT
 IMPORTING HI-TECH WORKERS

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:05.000
SHOULD BE AN ALTERNATIVE
 FOR PROPERLY TRAINING

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:07.000
OUR WORKFORCE HERE IN GERMANY.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:10.000
AND WE BLAME BOTH
 CORPORATIONS AND THE GOVERNMENT

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:12.000
FOR ALLOWING THIS TO HAPPEN.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:16.000
WHAT THE GERMAN FEDERATION
 OF TRADE UNIONS PROPOSES

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:18.000
IS PROPER TRAINING AT HOME

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.000
ALONG WITH
 AN OPEN IMMIGRATION POLICY.

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.000
[MAN TRANSLATING SCHWESINGER]

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
FOR US GERMANS
 IT'S STILL HARD TO ACCEPT

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:27.000
THAT THERE ARE PEOPLE
 IN COUNTRIES SUCH AS INDIA

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.000
WHO CAN HELP US ON OUR WAY
 TO THE INFORMATION AGE.

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:33.000
THE GREEN CARD PROGRAM
 IS THE FIRST STEP.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:34.000
I DON'T THINK IT'S ENOUGH,

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:36.000
BUT IT'S A MOVE
 IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:41.000
NARRATOR: SIX MONTHS
 INTO THE GREEN CARD PROGRAM

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.000
ONLY 2,000
 FOREIGN HI-TECH SPECIALISTS

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:44.000
HAVE APPLIED
 TO COME TO GERMANY.

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:46.000
SO REPRESENTATIVES

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:48.000
OF THE FRANKFURT ECONOMIC
 DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:50.000
ARE GOING ABROAD TO ATTRACT
 HI-TECH SPECIALISTS

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:52.000
AND INVESTORS.

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:54.000
[MAN TRANSLATING SCHWESINGER]

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.000
WE ASSIST FOREIGN COMPANIES

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:58.000
TO START UP OPERATIONS
 IN FRANKFURT.

00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:01.000
WE ALSO TRAVEL ABROAD
 TO INDIA FOR EXAMPLE

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:03.000
WHERE WE RECENTLY MET
 WITH BUSINESS EXECUTIVES

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:05.000
TO ANSWER
 ALL KINDS OF QUESTIONS

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:08.000
FROM TAXES
 TO LABOR REGULATIONS.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:11.000
[TECHNO MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:16.000
NARRATOR:
 FOREIGNERS COMING TO FRANKFURT

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:18.000
OF COURSE WOULD WANT TO KNOW
 ABOUT WORKING CONDITIONS,

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:20.000
BUT WHAT REALLY
 SEEMS TO ATTRACT NEWCOMERS

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
IS ITS INTERNATIONAL
 AND MULTICULTURAL FLAVOR.

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:29.000
[MAN TRANSLATING PREWO]

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:31.000
FOR FRANKFURT IT'S COOL

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:32.000
TO HAVE SUCH
 GREAT ENTERTAINMENT INPUT

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:35.000
FROM PEOPLE
 OF SO MANY DIFFERENT CULTURES.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:37.000
EVEN THOUGH A LOT OF THEM
 WERE BORN IN FRANKFURT,

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:39.000
THEY STILL KEEP
 THEIR CULTURAL BACKGROUND

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.000
THROUGH THEIR PARENTS,
 RELATIVES OR TRIPS HOME.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.000
THESE PEOPLE
 ARE GIVING FRANKFURT

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:45.000
A REAL INTERNATIONAL FLAVOR.

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:48.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING HABTEMARIAM]

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:49.000
WHENEVER I GO TO A CLUB

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.000
I LIKE TO THINK MEN LOOK AT ME

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:56.000
BECAUSE I'M A WOMAN
 AND NOT BECAUSE OF MY COLOR.

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:59.000
SURE, IN FRANKFURT MY COLOR
 IS AN EYE CATCHER.

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.000
IT MAKES ME
 INTERESTING AND EXOTIC.

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:04.000
THIS I LIKE TO CALL
 "POSITIVE RACISM."

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:09.000
[MAN TRANSLATING ROSETTI]

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:12.000
THE ENTIRE CITY, FRANKFURT,
 IS FULL OF FOREIGNERS.

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:15.000
WE COME FROM EUROPE
 AND EVERYWHERE ELSE.

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:17.000
AND THE MUSIC WE PLAY HERE
 IN MY CLUB,

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.000
EVERYTHING FROM JAZZ TO LATIN,

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:22.000
SEEMS TO BRING
 DIFFERENT PEOPLE TOGETHER.

00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:24.000
PEOPLE FROM DIFFERENT CULTURES.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:31.000
[MAN TRANSLATING GOLDMAN]

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:33.000
A LOT OF THINGS
 WILL HAPPEN HERE.

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:35.000
LIFE WILL PULSATE
 IN THIS COMPLEX.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.000
RESTAURANTS, NEW MEDIA,

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:39.000
EVERYTHING WILL HAPPEN.

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:41.000
IT WON'T BE
 A NINE TO FIVE ENVIRONMENT.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:43.000
HERE PEOPLE WILL
 WORK AND HAVE FUN

00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:44.000
AROUND THE CLOCK.

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:49.000
AS YOU CAN SEE
THE ROOM IS NOW EMPTY,

00:15:49.000 --> 00:15:52.000
BUT HOPEFULLY IT WILL BE
FILLED WITH YOUNG PEOPLE

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:53.000
WITH GREAT IDEAS,

00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:55.000
BRINGING UP
 NEW COMPANY START-UPS

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:57.000
IN THE INTERNET FIELD,
 SOFTWARE,

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:58.000
I.T., TELECOMMUNICATION.

00:15:58.000 --> 00:16:01.000
SO, WE ARE STANDING
 AT THE MOMENT IN THE HEART OF

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:03.000
WHICH IS CALLED THE BIGGEST
 INCUBATOR IN GERMANY

00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:05.000
FOR INTERNET START-UPS.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:07.000
IN HI-TECH BUSINESS
I SEE A CHANCE.

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:09.000
SO, BECAUSE THIS IS
THE FUTURE ECONOMY.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:13.000
IT WILL BE EVERY FIFTH JOB
WILL BE IN INTERNET.

00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:16.000
THAT WAS THE REASON WHY
I JOINED THE SNACKER COMPANY

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:17.000
HERE IN GERMANY.

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:19.000
I DON'T CARE
 THE PLACE I WORK AT.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:21.000
I MEAN, IT COULD BE
 BANGLADESH OR FRANKFURT.

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:23.000
FRANKFURT IS NOT A CITY,

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:25.000
FRANKFURT IS A CHALLENGE.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.000
AS A BLACK AMERICAN

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:32.000
IT'S ALWAYS GONNA BE
A VISIBLE FACTOR,

00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:34.000
'CAUSE YOU CAN FEEL IT
THROUGH A GLANCE,

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.000
YOU CAN FEEL IT
THROUGH A STARE,

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:39.000
YOU CAN FEEL IT THROUGH
SOME SORT OF BODY MOVEMENT

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:43.000
THAT, YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE NOT WANTED.

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:46.000
THIS WAS BASICALLY
 TO GIVE RESPECT

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:48.000
TO A VERY GOOD
 FRIEND OF MINE.

00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:49.000
THAT WAS MY CAT.

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:51.000
AND THAT WAS FELIX.

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:53.000
HE LIVED TO BE 20 YEARS OLD.

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:57.000
BEING A JEWISH-AMERICAN
 IN FRANKFURT

00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.000
IS SOMEWHAT OF A CHALLENGE.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:02.000
ONE OF THE BIGGEST SURPRISES

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:04.000
THAT I HAVE FOUND,
AND PERHAPS ONE OF THE SADDEST,

00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:06.000
IS THAT WHEN WE GO TO WORSHIP,

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:10.000
THERE ARE ALWAYS POLICE CARS,
 THERE'S AN ELECTRONIC GATE,

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:14.000
A BANDED TRAP TO GET INTO
 THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.000
WHERE OUR WORSHIP SERVICES
 ARE HELD.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:20.000
[MAN TRANSLATING GOLDMAN]

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:22.000
THIS DOESN'T BOTHER ME AT ALL.

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.000
I'M FULLY ASSIMILATED.
 I LIVE IN FRANKFURT.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:27.000
I'M A FRANKFURT BOY
 AND I DON'T HAVE ANY PROBLEM

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:29.000
WITH ANTI-SEMITISM.

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.000
SOMETIMES I HEAR ABOUT IT
 FROM FRIENDS,

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:34.000
BUT I'VE NEVER HAD ANY PROBLEM.

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:40.000
NARRATOR: NOT FAR FROM
 THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:42.000
IN THE DOWNTOWN AREA
 OF FRANKFURT

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.000
YOU'LL FIND
 A LARGE TURKISH COMMUNITY

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:47.000
AND HIDDEN AMONG SHOPS,
 RESTAURANTS AND OFFICES,

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:50.000
YOU'LL COME TO
 A TURKISH MOSQUE.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:52.000
FOR DECADES GERMANS DISMISSED

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:54.000
THE VALUE
 OF CULTURAL DIVERSITY.

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:56.000
THEY CONSIDERED RELIGIOUS
 AND ETHNIC DIFFERENCES

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.000
AS NEGATIVE
 TO NATIONAL INTEREST

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:01.000
AND A THREAT
 TO GERMAN CULTURE AND IDENTITY.

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.000
NEVERTHELESS, THE LARGE
 TURKISH COMMUNITY IN FRANKFURT

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:05.000
HAS MANAGED
 TO MAINTAIN AND FOSTER

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:08.000
ITS OWN RELIGIOUS
 AND CULTURAL IDENTITY.

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:11.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING SAHIN]

00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:14.000
MY WHOLE FAMILY HAS LIVED
 IN FRANKFURT FOR 30 YEARS.

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.000
WE DON'T FEEL LIKE STRANGERS.

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:19.000
HERE WE CAN KEEP OUR TURKISH
 CULTURE AND TRADITIONS.

00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:23.000
SO, FOR US NOTHING
 HAS CHANGED IN 30 YEARS.

00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:27.000
WE'RE STILL TURKS
 AND WE WILL RETURN TO TURKEY.

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.000
THAT IS OUR DREAM.

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:33.000
NARRATOR:
 MANY TURKISH IMMIGRANTS

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:34.000
DREAM OF RETURNING HOME

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:37.000
DRIVING THE SYMBOLS
 OF THEIR SUCCESS.

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:39.000
BUT THE NEW GENERATION
 OF TURKS IN FRANKFURT

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:42.000
NO LONGER HAS THIS DREAM.

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:44.000
THEY SEE THEMSELVES
 AS FRANKFURTERS

00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.000
HOWEVER,
 THEY OFTEN GET TOGETHER

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:48.000
TO CELEBRATE
 THEIR TURKISH HERITAGE.

00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:55.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING  G T]

00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:56.000
DEEP INSIDE ME,

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.000
I STILL KEEP MY TURKISH ROOTS,

00:18:57.000 --> 00:19:00.000
TRADITIONS AND WAY OF THINKING.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:03.000
ALL OF THIS COMES
 FROM MY UPBRINGING,

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:05.000
BUT I'M A GERMAN CITIZEN NOW.

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:07.000
AND THIS COMBINATION IS NICE,

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:09.000
BUT IT CONFUSES ME
 A LITTLE BIT.

00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:13.000
I COULDN'T SAY WHETHER I'M
 A HUNDRED PERCENT GERMAN,

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:16.000
OR A HUNDRED PERCENT TURK.

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:17.000
[MAN TRANSLATING GERMAN MAN]

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:20.000
WE FRANKFURTERS ARE USED
 TO PEOPLE FROM ABROAD,

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:22.000
WE'RE NOT ALWAYS HAPPY
 WITH THEIR BEHAVIOR

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:24.000
AND SOME OF THEIR
 INTOLERANT BELIEFS,

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:28.000
BUT WELL-MEANING AND DECENT
 PEOPLE ARE WELCOME.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:29.000
NARRATOR: THERE ARE
 CERTAINLY MANY GERMANS

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:31.000
WILLING TO ACCEPT
 TURKISH GERMANS,

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:33.000
SUCH AS MERAL  G T.

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:35.000
BUT THERE ARE OTHERS
 WHO ARE NOT.

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:37.000
[MAN TRANSLATING SCHLIERER]

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:39.000
I THINK ESPECIALLY OUR YOUTH

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:40.000
IS FACING A SERIOUS PROBLEM.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:42.000
IN THEIR OWN CITIES
 AND COMMUNITIES

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:45.000
THEY NO LONGER FEEL LIKE
 THEY ARE IN THEIR OWN COUNTRY.

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:47.000
THEY FEEL LIKE FOREIGNERS
 IN THEIR OWN COUNTRY

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.000
AND THEY ARE NOT ALLOWED
 TO ENTER CERTAIN AREAS,

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:52.000
BECAUSE THESE HAVE BECOME
 TURKISH OCCUPIED ZONES.

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:54.000
NATURALLY,
 THIS IS A RACIAL PROBLEM,

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:56.000
WHICH WILL LEAD
 TO CONFRONTATION.

00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:59.000
[CROWD CHANTING IN GERMAN]

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:01.000
[MAN TRANSLATING BRINK]

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:03.000
A FUNDAMENTAL PRINCIPLE
 OF THE FASCIST IDEOLOGY

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.000
IS RACISM.

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:08.000
AND FASCISTS REALLY BELIEVE
 THERE'S SOMETHING SPECIAL

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:10.000
ABOUT THE GERMAN PEOPLE,
 WHATEVER THAT MEANS.

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:13.000
THERE ISN'T SUCH A THING
 AS "THE GERMAN PEOPLE."

00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:14.000
WE'VE HAD IMMIGRANTS
 COMING TO GERMANY

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:17.000
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING
 MRS. EBRAHIM HANY]

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.000
WE'RE VERY HAPPY HERE.

00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:23.000
[MAN TRANSLATING
 MR. EBRAHIM HANY]

00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:24.000
WE LIVE HERE LIKE A FAMILY.

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:26.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING
 MRS. EBRAHIM HANY]

00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:29.000
LIKE A FAMILY, SOMEHOW
 THIS IS OUR COUNTRY NOW.

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:31.000
NARRATOR: FOR MANY FOREIGNERS
 GERMANY IS HOME.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:33.000
AND FOR SECOND AND THIRD
 GENERATION IMMIGRANTS

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:36.000
THIS IS THE ONLY HOME
 THEY KNOW.

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:38.000
[MAN TRANSLATING LEE]

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:39.000
MY PROBLEM IS THAT

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:41.000
I WAS BORN AND GREW UP
 IN GERMANY.

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:43.000
AND I FEEL GERMAN,

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:45.000
BUT I DON'T LOOK GERMAN.

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:47.000
AND IN KOREA I LOOK KOREAN,

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:49.000
BUT I DON'T FEEL KOREAN.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:50.000
BUT THE FUNNY THING IS THAT

00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:53.000
WHEN GERMANS SEE ME,
 THEY SEE ONLY AN ASIAN.

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:54.000
NO MORE.

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:56.000
AND THEY THINK,
 MAYBE HE'S A TOURIST.

00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.000
MAYBE A STUDENT.

00:20:57.000 --> 00:20:59.000
JUST A FOREIGNER.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:11.000
I GREW UP WITH GERMAN FRIENDS
 IN A GERMAN SCHOOL,

00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:14.000
BUT MY PARENTS ALWAYS TRIED
 TO BRING ME UP THE KOREAN WAY

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:17.000
AND TO MAKE A KOREAN OUT OF ME.

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:20.000
THEY WANTED ME TO THINK
 AND BEHAVE LIKE A KOREAN.

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:24.000
NARRATOR: 24 YEARS
 AFTER YUNG LEE'S PARENTS

00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:26.000
IMMIGRATED TO FRANKFURT,

00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:28.000
THE CITY HAS THE LARGEST
 KOREAN COMMUNITY IN EUROPE.

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:30.000
AND KOREAN PARENTS
 ARE STILL TRYING

00:21:30.000 --> 00:21:32.000
TO BRING UP THEIR KIDS
 THE KOREAN WAY.

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:34.000
[SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:37.000 --> 00:21:39.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING LEE]

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:41.000
I THINK IT'S VERY IMPORTANT
 FOR OUR KIDS TO LEARN

00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:43.000
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE KOREAN

00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:46.000
AND THAT KOREA IS STILL
 PART OF THEIR LIVES.

00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:48.000
AND FOR US
 IT'S IMPORTANT

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:50.000
TO TEACH OUR KIDS
 THE KOREAN LANGUAGE,

00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:51.000
BECAUSE THIS IS ESSENTIAL

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:54.000
IF WE WANT THEM
 TO KEEP OUR CULTURE.

00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:59.000
NARRATOR: AT THE FRANKFURT
 KOREAN CULTURE SCHOOL

00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:01.000
EVERY SATURDAY HUNDREDS OF KIDS

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:02.000
SPEND THEIR DAY IN CLASSROOMS

00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:05.000
LEARNING TO THINK AND BEHAVE
 LIKE KOREANS.

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:06.000
BUT I THE SCHOOLYARD THEY PLAY

00:22:06.000 --> 00:22:09.000
ACCORDING TO
 THE BEST GERMAN TRADITION.

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:12.000
[MAN TRANSLATING YUNG LEE]

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:14.000
I FEEL GERMAN, BUT GERMANS
 ONLY SEE ME AS AN ASIAN

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:16.000
WHO SPEAKS FLUENT GERMAN.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.000
THEY SEE AN ASIAN
 BORN IN GERMANY

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.000
WHO SPEAKS GERMAN PERFECTLY.

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:23.000
BUT THEY STILL SEE ME
 AS KOREAN, JAPANESE OR CHINESE,

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:25.000
BUT NOT GERMAN.

00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:29.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING
 WOLF-ALMANASREH]

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:31.000
GLOBALIZATION
 HAS MADE IT VERY CLEAR:

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:34.000
THE FOREIGNERS WHO COME
 TO GERMANY ARE IMMIGRANTS

00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:36.000
AND LOTS OF THEM
 WILL STAY HERE,

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:39.000
AS WELL AS THEIR CHILDREN
 AND GRANDCHILDREN.

00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:51.000
NARRATOR: JUST LIKE
 IN THE MUSIC VIDEOS THEY WATCH,

00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:53.000
IN FRANKFURT, TEENAGERS
 OF ALL RACES AND NATIONALITIES

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:55.000
ALREADY ACCEPT EACH OTHER

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:58.000
WITHOUT MAKING
 A BIG DEAL OF IT.

00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:01.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING RABENAU]

00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:03.000
IN MY HIGH SCHOOL
 WE HAVE STUDENTS

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:06.000
FROM DIFFERENT COUNTRIES.

00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:10.000
WE HAVE KIDS FROM ITALY,
 SPAIN, POLAND, SERBIA,

00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:12.000
AND WE ALL GET ALONG FINE.

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:15.000
WE'RE ALL FRIENDS.
 IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:18.000
[MAN TRANSLATING STRANSKY]

00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:20.000
ON THE STREETS ONE KNOWS
 THAT KIDS FROM AFRICA

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:23.000
ARE MORE AGGRESSIVE THAN KIDS
 FROM WEST OR EAST GERMANY,

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:24.000
OR ANY OTHER COUNTRY.

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:27.000
KIDS FROM DOWN THERE
 ARE MUCH MORE AGGRESSIVE.

00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:30.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING RABENAU]

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:33.000
GERMAN KIDS DON'T HAVE
 BIG PROBLEMS WITH FOREIGNERS.

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:37.000
OFTEN THE FOREIGN KIDS
 CREATE THEIR OWN PROBLEMS.

00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:39.000
[MAN TRANSLATING STRANSKY]

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:42.000
AND THEN WHEN DRUGS
 COME INTO THE PICTURE,

00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:44.000
SMOKING WHATEVER YOU CAN GET,
 MOSTLY GRASS,

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:46.000
GANGS BEGIN TO FIGHT
 FOR CONTROL OF THE STREETS.

00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:47.000
THEN EVERYTHING GOES,

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:49.000
BETRAYALS, THREATS, MURDER.

00:23:49.000 --> 00:23:50.000
ANYTHING YOU CAN IMAGINE.

00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.000
NARRATOR: IN FRANKFURT
 DIFFERENCES AMONG YOUNG PEOPLE

00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:59.000
ARE NO LONGER BASED
 ON NATIONALITY OR RACE,

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:00.000
BUT ON SOCIAL PROBLEMS

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:02.000
WHICH ARE THE SAME
 IN ANY GLOBAL CITY.

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:03.000
[WOMAN TRANSLATING
 WOLF-ALMANASREH]

00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:05.000
GERMAN AND FOREIGN KIDS
 ARE GROWING UP TOGETHER.

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:07.000
THEY GO TO THE SAME SCHOOLS

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.000
AND THEY LIVE
 IN THE SAME NEIGHBORHOODS.

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:13.000
THIS IS AN EXAMPLE
 OF MULTI-CULTURALISM.

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:16.000
[MAN TRANSLATING ERZAN]

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:18.000
HOW DO OUR KIDS GET ALONG?

00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:19.000
LIKE KIDS ANYWHERE.

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.000
THEIR ETHNICITY DOESN'T MATTER.

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:23.000
NATURALLY,
 SOMETIMES THERE ARE CONFLICTS.

00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:24.000
KIDS ARE KIDS.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:26.000
THEY MIGHT FIGHT
 OVER A BOOK OR A TOY,

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:29.000
BUT ETHNIC DIFFERENCES
 MEAN NOTHING TO THEM.

00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:32.000
THERE WE HAVE TOTAL PEACE.

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:37.000
ROLF BREUER: I THINK
 THAT WE SHOULD DEVELOP

00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:40.000
INTO AN OPEN SOCIETY,

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:42.000
COMPARABLE TO OTHER NATIONS.

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.000
WE ARE NOT
THE FIRST ONE TO INVENT

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:49.000
A PROPER EDUCATED
IMMIGRATION POLICY.

00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:51.000
WE JUST LOOK
AT THE UNITED STATES,

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:54.000
WE LOOK AT OTHER DEVELOPED
COUNTRIES IN EUROPE,

00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:55.000
THEN WE SEE WHAT WE SHOULD DO,

00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:57.000
AND I THINK WE ARE
ON A VERY GOOD WAY.

00:24:57.000 --> 00:24:59.000
[SPEAKING GERMAN,
ALL REPEATING SAME PHRASE]

00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:01.000
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:03.000
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:25:11.000 --> 00:25:13.000
NOT FRANKFURT, KENTUCKY.

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:15.000
NOT FRANKFURT, INDIANA,
THE STATE WHERE I'M FROM,

00:25:15.000 --> 00:25:19.000
BUT "FRANKFURT HIER AM MAIN."

